problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-number-of-balloons/description/

Intuition
to determine the maximum number of times the world balloon can be formed , i first count the freq of each characters required to cuild the world usind a hash map .

next i count the freq of every character present in the input string TEXT , for each required character i calaculate how many complete copies of baloon that character can support by performing integer division ,

have[ch] = freq of ch in text
need[ch] = freq of ch in balloon

the expression have[ch] // ned[ch] gives maximum number of complete words that can be formed using that particular charcater.

Since every character is required to build the word , the overall answer is limited by the character that can support the fewest copies, therefore i return the minimum value among all required characters

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(7) + O(n) + O(5) = O(n)

Space complexity:
O(26) = O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def maxNumberOfBalloons(self, text: str) -> int:
        s = "balloon"
        need = {}
        for ch in s:
            need[ch] = need.get(ch,0) + 1
        have = {}
        for ch in text:
            have[ch] = have.get(ch,0) + 1

       
        formed = []
        for i ,ch in enumerate(need):
            formed.append(have.get(ch,0) // need.get(ch,0))
        
        return min(formed)
